Here is a riddle for you: how do you call someone who talks when everyone has stopped listening? The answer is Jamel Cherbib. This was an awful class. He would read the book with us with 3 hours, with his extremely loud voice and rapid speech flow. Doesn't prepare you for the final. Doesn't answer questions; he just repeats what he previously said.

pathetic prof. so incredibly rude, doesn't teach, reads from slides. i can't stress how much i hate this guy, horrible person. midterm and final were full of mistakes, some questions weren't even questions, just statements we were expected to answer. the whole midterm, 50 questions was true or false. burn in hell.  an ex marketing major

Absolutely awful! Prof will ask you to participate in class, but sets way too many barriers! He will interrupt you, tell you you're wrong, or go too fast through the material for you to keep up! Exams have completely irrelevant questions, and will not even answer basic questions. For our class he did not even have TAs, so we NEVER got anything back

If you want a prof who yells at the top of his lungs all class, reads out slideshows he download from the textbook giving you no explanations, is rude to students, and gives you no information for exams this is the class for you! For our final exam we were told 2 days before it was cumulative, and were given no information on what to focus on.

rComments: He is hard to follow and makes unfair exams.  If you are an immersion student I do not recommend you take his classes because he speaks VERY fast and removes slides from his presentations at random so if you don't take notes fast enough you will miss the material completely. 10% of the course grade is also for class participation.

This teacher is not very good. Really intelligent prof but he is really not a good teacher. Incredibly long classes with discustingly long powerpoints. If you can avoid his class. He made a very interesting class on Social Media seem extremely tedious and very very boring.
